23/09/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivica Racan met with the ruling coalition partners Monday (22 September) and confirmed that general elections would be scheduled for 23 November. The proposed timetable would be submitted to the president, who by law sets the date for elections, said Racan. He added that the government plans to complete work on the European Commission's lengthy questionnaire, an important step in the country's path to EU accession, by 9 October.
In other news, union workers say they will block major seaports for an hour on Thursday. Leaders say the move is in protest of the cabinet's refusal to withdraw from parliament a controversial draft law on maritime goods and seaports. (HINA, BBC - 22/09/03)
